---
import { Container } from "@components/odyssey-theme";
import Layout from "../layouts/Page.astro";
---

<Layout>
  <Container>
    <h1>About</h1>
    <p>
      Welcome to our chart components documentation! Our dynamic chart
      components allow you to create and customize various types of charts to
      visualize your data effectively. Here’s an overview of the functionalities
      offered by each component:
    </p>
    <h2>Line Chart Component</h2>
    <p>
      The Line Chart Component is designed to create line charts for visualizing
      trends and changes over time. You can customize the following aspects:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>
        <strong>Line Colors:</strong> Adjust the colors of the lines using color
        input fields. You can also copy the color code to the clipboard for reuse.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Line Width:</strong> Modify the width of the lines to fit your data
        representation needs.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Point Size:</strong> Change the size of the points on the line to
        enhance data highlighting.
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Pie Chart Component</h2>
    <p>
      The Pie Chart Component is designed to provide a visual representation of
      data in a pie chart format. You can customize the following aspects:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>
        <strong>Slice Colors:</strong> Adjust the colors of each slice using color
        input fields. You can also copy the color code to the clipboard for reuse.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Slice Width:</strong> Modify the width of the slices to fit your
        data representation needs.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Inner Radius:</strong> Change the inner radius of the pie chart to
        create a donut chart effect.
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Bar Chart Component</h2>
    <p>
      The Bar Chart Component allows you to create bar charts with customizable
      properties to visualize your data in a clear and concise manner. You can
      adjust the following settings:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>
        <strong>Bar Colors:</strong> Customize the colors of the bars using color
        input fields. You can copy the color code to the clipboard for easy access.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Bar Width:</strong> Alter the width of the bars to suit your data
        representation requirements.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Legends and Labels:</strong> The component includes legends and labels
        for better data interpretation and clarity.
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Using the Components</h2>
    <p>
      To use these components, simply integrate them into your project and
      configure them using the provided forms. Each component is designed to be
      responsive, ensuring optimal viewing on various devices. The components
      make use of the <strong>@nivo</strong> library, known for its powerful and
      flexible charting capabilities.
    </p>
    <p>
      We hope these components help you visualize your data effectively. If you
      have any questions or need further assistance, please don’t hesitate to
      reach out.
    </p>
  </Container>
</Layout>
